Here’s a dope YouTube video I just dropped on building wealth & creating Family S.O.P’s
•

Family Standard Operating Procedures are the guidelines that easy family should have in place so that the generations that follow have the actual blueprint to sustain wealth.
•

What usually happens is, one generation acquires the wealth through learning the rules to the game & making the investments.
•

Then they usually pass the wealth to the next generation who saw the grind so they may appreciate it.
•

But by the 3rd generation,there’s no ties to the struggle, their entire life is on a silver platter, wealth is normalize, but there’s no blueprint to keep it & no reference point for them to look back on and say this is where we come from.
•

Go check out the full YouTube clip on Family S.O.P’s on my YouTube Channel.
•

node.text:
•

I didnt start this journey because i wanted to make a lot of money.
•

I seriously started because investing saved my life, &  i knew the streets was taking so many of us away.
•

I knew that if this could save my life, i knew if people knew my story & what i’ve been through, then they’d relate to me & it’ll save their life.
•

Nothing against rappers or entertainers, but i seriously lived a dangerous life.
•

and everyday i wanted out, but i didn’t know how to get out. I didn’t think there was nothing else for me to be.
•

Investing showed me different, so i knew in my heart, if i told my story & kept learning about building wealth. I COULD CHANGE LIVES.
•

My starting this mission had nothing to do with me. The only reason you wanna start is because you looking at how much money you can make.
•

Impact is a better business plan than how much money you can make.
•

Impact people’s lives & you’ll make more money than you’ve ever seen.
•

Wanna thank my brother @1jeremyanderson for letting me speak at his NEXT LEVEL SPEAKERS EVENT!
•

Big Trap🏚⚖️🏚⚖️

node.text:
Perspective is everything.
•

The educational system & entertainment has truly played a trick on how we see money & time.
•

We’ll Work for 40 years just to retire (and some have to get a job after that)
•

But won’t take the time to get educated on how to invest and buy back that time.
•

The real real risk in life is NOT investing. Because nothing else gives you control of your financial future.
•

And alot of americans (especially black and brown) don’t even have a career, so it’s job to job until you can get social security.
•

And we all know, with $29 trillion in debt & growing, it’s a good chance that won’t be around when it’s your turn.
•

Investing isn’t made to save you today, but it does create an amazing tomorrow.
•

Dividends won’t pay ALL your billS today, but compounding and reinvesting them can be amazing cash flow tomorrow.
•

You won’t always be this young, fine, energetic, handsome, amazing, beautiful & active all your life.
•

So yes, live it up, but also prepare for tomorrow, because it’s inevitable.
•

And the worst thing is to know you had the opportunity & you didn’t take advantage of it. You won’t get that time back.
•

This is why Fintech is a must have in your portfolio NOW.
•

We are just scratching the surface & the growth in it is astronomical.
•

This industry will truly close the wealth gap for all those who choose to get in the game.
•

For those who decide to sit this out, you’ll be in the “I know i should” have” group 10-15 years from now when the world is shifting again.
•

•

node.text:
As leaders & Educators we must understand that we all will come under great scrutiny. And our people have that right.
•

They have been lied to, scammed, mislead & sometimes ruined from bad experiences.
•

It’s easy for us to say, how can u not know that was a scam? Why didn’t you use common sense?
•

Well, when you’re in survival mode, it ain’t always easy to see things for what they are.
•

Sometimes you go against your better judgement because you want a sense of relief.
•

A many times in my life i risked my life and freedom because is wanted relief.
•

Our people have trauma on so many levels, we must remember to show them the way, not shame them or belittle them.
•

We must have compassion & patience at all times.
•

It’s a long journey ahead, but there’s truly freedom on the other side. And if we are serious about leading them there (no matter what our method is) we must always show up as leaders.
•

I challege us all to give more and more value to the culture, to the community. Go out our your way to show up and push your limits on education.
•

I do know there’s more love than hate, our community has always searched for leadership. And the dope part is, They don’t care if you’re not perfect.
•

They will follow you, but only if you walk with them & not ahead of them.
•

When You walk amongst them, they will fight for you & not against you.
•

True leadership is always about The PEOPLE!!
•

To anyone who i have ever been impatient with on this journey, I apologize for that. I was still  developing as a leader.
•

I still am, but as i grow i hope u all see how i am evoling to represent those who rock with me Well.
•
